<item>
            <title>[JDK-8338314] JFR: Split JFRCheckpoint VM operation</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8338314</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Investigating JFR crashes is a bit tedious, as Events section in hs_err shows just:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
Event: 3.006 Executing VM operation: JFRCheckpoint&lt;br/&gt;
Event: 3.006 Executing VM operation: JFRCheckpoint done&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
What is that JFRCheckpoint doing is unclear, because it can do two separate things: clear or write. It would be good if we could disambiguate the two. Since there are only two flavors of checkpoint, I think we can just split the VMOp into two more precisely named ones, so it gives us e.g.:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
Event: 2.462 Executing VM operation: JFRSafepointClear&lt;br/&gt;
Event: 2.463 Executing VM operation: JFRSafepointClear done&lt;br/&gt;
```</description>
